episodes.title: Oh. My. Gaga!
episodes.plot: The queens walk into the workroom for the first time; Lady Gaga guest judges; Queens must perform in an epic pageant in which they style their fashionable hometown and Lady Gaga looks.

episodes.title: She Done Already Done Brought It On
episodes.plot: Lisa Kudrow visits; the queens must perform in an epic cheer battle; the B-52's guest judge.

episodes.title: Draggily Ever After
episodes.plot: The queens must create fairytale drag princesses, and transform themselves into sassy sidekicks. With guest judges Todrick Hall and Cheyenne Jackson (American Horror Story).

episodes.title: Good Morning Bitches
episodes.plot: The queens join the cutthroat Morning Talk Show wars. Naya Rivera (Glee) and Jeffrey Bowyer-Chapman (UnREAL) guest judge.

episodes.title: Reality Stars: The Musical
episodes.plot: The queens are tasked with doing a lipsync performance of Kardashian: The Musical. Guest judges include Meghan Trainor and Todrick Hall.

episodes.title: Snatch Game
episodes.plot: The queens impersonate celebrities in a quick-witted TV game show. With guest judges Candis Cayne and Denis O'Hare.

episodes.title: 9021-HO
episodes.plot: The queens act in a classic 90s high school drama, directed by original Beverly Hills 90210 stars Tori Spelling and Jennie Garth.

episodes.title: RuPaul Roast
episodes.plot: This week, the queens roast Michelle Visage, in addition to guest judges Fortune Fiemster and Tamar Braxton.

episodes.title: Your Pilot's on Fire
episodes.plot: The queens create, write and star in their own TV pilots. Noah Galvin (The Real O'Neals) and QVC queen Lisa Robertson guest judge.

episodes.title: Makeovers: Crew Better Work
episodes.plot: The queens make over members of the "Drag Race" crew; singer Kesha and gown designer Zaldy guest judge.

episodes.title: Gayest Ball Ever
episodes.plot: The queens compete in a queer culture pageant, and design outfits inspired by the Village People. Actress Andie MacDowell (Groundhog Day) and supermodel Joan Smalls guest judge.

episodes.title: Category Is
episodes.plot: The queens must write and perform a rap on RuPaul's new hit single, and guest RuPaul's podcast with Michelle Visage. Style superstar Carson Kressley and the hilarious Ross Matthews guest judge.

episodes.title: Reunited
episodes.plot: One week away from the finale, the contestants gather around to discuss the season's biggest moments. All T, All Shade.

episodes.title: Grand Finale
episodes.plot: In an epic, show-stopping finale, RuPaul crowns America's Next Drag Superstar.
